ctionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French: habitational name, with fused preposition <i>d(e)</i> ‘from’, for someone from Aire, the name of a few places in various parts of France, e.g. in Ardennes and Pas-de-Calais."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Théobald","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>þeud</i> ‘people, race’ + <i>bald</i> ‘bold, brave’. The first element was altered under the influence of Greek <i>theos</i> ‘god’. This name was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Ier","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["and Norwegian vernacular form of   Peter ."],"variants":[{"name":"Peter","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Théobald Ier D'AIRE was born in 1080, in Aire-sur-la-Lys, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, his father, Baudouin Ier D'AIRE, was 28 and his mother, Marie de NEDONCHEL, was 29. He married Blanche DE BAILLEUL about 1109. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1127, in his hometown, at the age of 47."},"et":{"1080–1127":"1080–1127","1092–1148":"1092–1148","1100–1163":"1100–1163","1110–1166":"1110–1166","1052–1093":"1052–1093","1051–1109":"1051–1109","1080":"1080","1110":"1110","1163":"1163","1052":"1052","1051":"1051","1093":"1093","1092":"1092","about 1109":"umbes 1109","1127":"1127","1148":"1148","1100":"1100","1166":"1166","1109":"1109","Aire-sur-la-Lys, 62014, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Aire-sur-la-Lys, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Strazeele, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Strazeele, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Aire-sur-la-Lys, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Aire-sur-la-Lys, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1080–1127":"1080–1127","1092–1148":"1092–1148","1100–1163":"1100–1163","1110–1166":"1110–1166","1052–1093":"1052–1093","1051–1109":"1051–1109","1080":"1080","1110":"1110","1163":"1163","1052":"1052","1051":"1051","1093":"1093","1092":"1092","about 1109":"noin 1109","1127":"1127","1148":"1148","1100":"1100","1166":"1166","1109":"1109","Aire-sur-la-Lys, 62014, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Aire-sur-la-Lys, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Ranska","Strazeele, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Strazeele, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Ranska","Aire-sur-la-Lys, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Aire-sur-la-Lys, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Ranska"},"fr":{"1080–1127":"1080–1127","1092–1148":"1092–1148","1100–1163":"1100–1163","1110–1166":"1110–1166","1052–1093":"1052–1093","1051–1109":"1051–1109","1080":"1080","1110":"1110","1163":"1163","1052":"1052","1051":"1051","1093":"1093","1092":"1092","about 1109":"environ 1109","1127":"1127","1148":"1148","1100":"1100","1166":"1166","1109":"1109","Aire-sur-la-Lys, 62014, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Aire-sur-la-Lys, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","Strazeele, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Strazeele, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","Aire-sur-la-Lys, P